    <text>
        <body>
            <head>181. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (<persName corresp="rech6OQ6N5EdBVhDo">Carlucci</persName>) to President
                    <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d181fn1">Source: National Security
                    Council, <orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security
                        Council</orgName> Institutional Files, SR Box 094, NSDD 256. Secret. Sent
                    for action. Prepared by <persName corresp="recwQ7GkdUfKar7pC">Brooks</persName>.
                    Copied to <persName corresp="recjlYSNpDHCqlk6w">Bush</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="recnIb7zTocHk4sWn">Regan</persName>. <persName
                        corresp="recwQ7GkdUfKar7pC">Brooks</persName>, Mahley, <persName
                        corresp="recASjYJjIDTjOXpN">Tobey</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="rec1MI7pNjlwnDZyR">Kraemer</persName>, and <persName
                        corresp="recSebTWtZht38y2p">Steiner</persName> sent the memorandum and
                    attachments to <persName corresp="rech6OQ6N5EdBVhDo">Carlucci</persName> for his
                    signature under a covering memorandum of January 12. (Ibid.) (S)</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="simple_right #right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1987-01-14"
                        >January 14, 1987</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Guidance for the Upcoming <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear
                        and Space Talks</rs> (<gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                    </gloss>) Negotiating Round</item>
            </list>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Issue</p>
            <p>To approve instructions for the seventh round of <rs type="event"
                    corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and Space Talks</rs> (<gloss
                    target="#t_NST_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                </gloss>) in Geneva.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Background</p>
            <p>The <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and Space Talks</rs> resume
                in Geneva on January 15.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
            <p>Overall negotiating instructions (<hi rendition="simple_italic">Tab A</hi>) and
                specific negotiating instructions for <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N"
                    >Defense and Space</rs> (<hi rendition="simple_italic">Tab B</hi>), <gloss
                    target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                </gloss> (<hi rendition="simple_italic">Tab C</hi>) and <gloss target="#t_INF_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recgLCwFE47waxYP9">INF</rs>
                </gloss> (<hi rendition="simple_italic">Tab D</hi>)<note n="2" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d181fn2">Attached but not printed, at Tab D, are the <gloss
                        target="#t_INF_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recgLCwFE47waxYP9">INF</rs>
                    </gloss> instructions.</note> have been prepared by the normal interagency
                process. I have attached a summary sheet for you to record your approval on each set
                of instructions. The overall instructions and the <rs type="event"
                    corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and Space</rs> instructions are agreed to by
                all agencies. One major and three minor disagreements exist with respect to the
                    <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                </gloss> and <gloss target="#t_INF_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recgLCwFE47waxYP9">INF</rs>
                </gloss> instructions. Minor issues and my recommendation are noted on the
                appropriate summary sheet.</p>
            <p>The major issue concerns our position that <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID">mobile</rs>
                <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                    <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBMs</rs>
                </gloss> should be banned for <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic"
                    >verification</rs> and stability reasons. <hi rendition="simple_italic">
                    <persName corresp="recZmD7Wil34KIjtu">Paul Nitze</persName>
                </hi> believes that the recent <rs type="topic" corresp="recCgPN2725pAs6HG"
                    >PEACEKEEPER</rs> decision means that our <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recbm2CDfl6YlSCnq">modernization</rs> program and negotiating position
                are inconsistent and that, therefore, we should alter our negotiating position to
                permit <rs type="topic" corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID">mobile missiles</rs>. His
                arguments are in a memorandum to you at <hi rendition="simple_italic">Tab
                    F</hi>,<note n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn3">
                    <persName corresp="recZmD7Wil34KIjtu">Nitze</persName>’s memorandum and the
                    contrary views expressed by <persName corresp="recCAUUmNdxvAWExm"
                        >Rowny</persName>, <persName corresp="recJgMRnt6OpkXR5T">Lehman</persName>,
                    and <persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName> are printed
                    above as <ref target="#d178">Documents 178</ref>, <ref target="#d177">177</ref>,
                        <ref target="#d179">179</ref>, and <ref target="#d180">180</ref>.</note>
                along with contrary views of your other senior <rs corresp="recQ5xJqddmHqhjNl"
                    type="topic">arms control</rs> advisors.</p>
            <p>
                <hi rendition="simple_italic">All other agencies</hi> oppose changing position now.
                I agree. We have been stressing <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic"
                    >verification</rs> of <rs type="topic" corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID">mobile
                    missiles</rs>; the Soviets have not been prepared to discuss the subject
                seriously. If we now accept <rs type="topic" corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID">mobile</rs>
                <pb facs="0820" n="793" xml:id="pg_793"/> missile deployment, with no quid from the
                Soviets and no progress on <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic"
                    >verification</rs>, we will lend credence to the erroneous view that the <rs
                    type="event" corresp="recrvfeHjk0YIZ1si">Administration</rs> has been wounded by
                    <rs type="event" corresp="reczBdFtXt9g39SHd">Iran</rs> and is eager for an
                agreement to restore its prestige. Therefore I recommend our position remain
                unchanged.</p>
            <p>The draft NSDD at <hi rendition="simple_italic">Tab E</hi>
                <note n="4" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn4">Printed below as <ref target="#d182"
                        >Document 182</ref>.</note> documents your approval of the instructions to
                our negotiators. It includes as attachments the individual instructions you have
                reviewed in <hi rendition="simple_italic">Tabs A through D</hi>.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
            <table cols="3">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">OK</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">NO</hi>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>That you review and initial each set of the proposed negotiating
                        instructions indicating your approval and sign the attached NSDD documenting
                        that approval.<note n="5" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn5">
                            <persName corresp="rech6OQ6N5EdBVhDo">Carlucci</persName> initialed
                            approval on behalf of <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq"
                                >Reagan</persName>, and wrote at the bottom of the memorandum:
                            “Instructions handled at 10:30 mtg w/ President 1/14/87.” No minutes of
                            the meeting were found.</note>
                    </cell>
                </row>
            </table>
            <frus:attachment xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
                <note>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Attachment</hi>
                </note>
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Paper Prepared in the <orgName
                            corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security Council</orgName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="6" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn6">Secret. Prepared by <persName
                            corresp="recwQ7GkdUfKar7pC">Brooks</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="simple_right #right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian"
                            notAfter="1987-01-14T10:30:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1987-01-12T23:59:59-05:00">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rendition="simple_centre">Overall Instructions—Round VII</p>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
                <p>The attached instructions<note n="7" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn7">Attached but
                        not printed is a draft telegram transmitting the overall
                        instructions.</note> are agreed to by all agencies. They provide overall
                    guidance not unique to specific negotiating areas. They direct the delegation
                    to:</p>
                <p>—Continue to build on past efforts to gain Soviet agreement to the text of
                    documents recording areas of agreement.</p>
                <p>—Reject Soviet attempts to hold progress in one area (especially <gloss
                        target="#t_INF_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recgLCwFE47waxYP9">INF</rs>
                    </gloss>) hostage to progress in other areas.</p>
                <p>—Give priority to 50% <rs type="topic" corresp="recHoFOsQcM4e5M4k">strategic
                        reductions</rs> and significant <gloss target="#t_INF_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recgLCwFE47waxYP9">INF</rs>
                    </gloss>
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="reccHhVr2uF3YAH0U">reductions</rs> rather than debate
                    Soviet allegations that the United States agreed in <rs type="event"
                        corresp="recY5TBKXKBIuAnWc">Reykjavik</rs> to eliminate all <rs type="topic"
                        corresp="recAynYh8uzxYGQRH">strategic offensive arms</rs>.</p>
                <pb facs="0821" n="794" xml:id="pg_794"/>
                <p>—Stress the importance of <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic"
                        >verification</rs> measures being negotiated concurrently with agreements on
                        <rs type="topic" corresp="recHoFOsQcM4e5M4k">reductions</rs>.</p>
                <p>—Stress the importance of Soviet <rs corresp="recMjLDCnI9cLa32M" type="topic"
                        >compliance</rs> with existing <rs corresp="recQ5xJqddmHqhjNl" type="topic"
                        >arms control</rs> agreements.</p>
                <p>—Reject Soviet efforts to introduce new areas (especially <rs
                        type="compound-subject" corresp="recFUg0jqFk2tUZ15">nuclear testing</rs>)
                    into these negotiations.</p>
                <p>There are no issues involved with these instructions.</p>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
                <table cols="3">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="simple_italic">OK</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="simple_italic">NO</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>That you approve the proposed overall negotiating instructions.<note
                                n="8" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn8">
                                <persName corresp="rech6OQ6N5EdBVhDo">Carlucci</persName> initialed
                                approval on behalf of <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq"
                                    >Reagan</persName>.</note>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </frus:attachment>
            <frus:attachment xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
                <note>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Attachment</hi>
                </note>
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Paper Prepared in the <orgName
                            corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security Council</orgName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="9" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn9">Secret. Prepared by <persName
                            corresp="recwQ7GkdUfKar7pC">Brooks</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="simple_right #right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian"
                            notAfter="1987-01-14T10:30:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1987-01-12T23:59:59-05:00">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rendition="simple_centre">
                    <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss> Instructions—Round VII</p>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
                <p>The attached <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss> instructions<note n="10" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn10">Attached but
                        not printed is a draft telegram transmitting the <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                            <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                        </gloss> instructions.</note> are agreed to by all agencies. They reiterate
                    our existing <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss> proposal, based on your <rs type="event" corresp="recY5TBKXKBIuAnWc"
                        >Reykjavik</rs> discussions, for a 50% reduction. Our proposal includes the
                    following key features:</p>
                <p>—A ceiling of 1600 <rs type="topic" corresp="recMGkwDnbHpEWvfN">strategic nuclear
                        deliver vehicles</rs> (<gloss target="#t_SNDV_1">
                        <rs type="topic" corresp="recMGkwDnbHpEWvfN">SNDVs</rs>
                    </gloss>) (<rs type="topic" corresp="recr08QgEMEm1Bk04">ballistic missiles</rs>
                    plus <rs type="topic" corresp="rectLhSs11Y4ZQ6zE">heavy bombers</rs>)</p>
                <p>—6000 total <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warheads</rs> (<gloss
                        target="#t_RV_1">RVs</gloss> plus <gloss target="#t_ALCM_1">
                        <rs corresp="rec3r8I0hO6jAW3Fm" type="topic">ALCMs</rs>
                    </gloss> plus <rs type="topic" corresp="rectLhSs11Y4ZQ6zE">heavy bombers</rs>
                    carrying <rs type="topic" corresp="recnvEYOcmY68IH3z">gravity bombs</rs> or <rs
                        type="topic" corresp="recJJ92wdIeZoqUpd">Short Range Attack Missiles</rs>),
                    with <rs corresp="recNg1LuXkmZCFR19" type="topic">sublimits</rs> of:</p>
                <quote>
                    <p>—4800 <rs type="topic" corresp="recr08QgEMEm1Bk04">ballistic missile</rs>
                        <gloss target="#t_RV_1">RVs</gloss>
                    </p>
                    <p>—3300 <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                            <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBM</rs>
                        </gloss>
                        <gloss target="#t_RV_1">RVs</gloss>
                    </p>
                    <p>—1650 <gloss target="#t_RV_1">RVs</gloss> on <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                            <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBMs</rs>
                        </gloss> other than silo-based medium or light <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                            <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBMs</rs>
                        </gloss> which carry less than 6 <gloss target="#t_RV_1">RVs</gloss>.</p>
                </quote>
                <p>—<rs type="topic" corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID">Mobile</rs>
                    <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                        <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBMs</rs>
                    </gloss> banned (DISAGREEMENT: SEE BELOW)</p>
                <p>—50% <rs corresp="reclksm3VX3UUxetF" type="topic">throw-weight</rs> reduction</p>
                <p>—<rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">Verification</rs> including:</p>
                <pb facs="0822" n="795" xml:id="pg_795"/>
                <quote>
                    <p>—<rs type="topic" corresp="recMHaxzFHPF55Bah">Data exchange</rs>
                    </p>
                    <p>—<rs type="topic" corresp="reclbsHvbXLer8sMP">On-site</rs> observation of
                        reductions</p>
                    <p>—Monitoring (including <rs type="topic" corresp="reclbsHvbXLer8sMP">on-site
                            inspection</rs>) of remaining inventories</p>
                    <p>—Non-interference with <rs corresp="recpKti8nkHOtxwgG" type="topic">national
                            technical means</rs> of <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic"
                            >verification</rs>
                    </p>
                </quote>
                <p>—Phased reductions to be completed by 1991</p>
                <p>—A mutually acceptable solution to limiting <rs type="topic"
                        corresp="recFTCG8rSp7cACBI">sea-launched cruise missiles</rs> which does <hi
                        rendition="simple_italic">not</hi> include them in the 1600/6000 limits
                    noted above.</p>
                <p>The instructions stress the importance the U.S. attaches to <rs
                        corresp="recNg1LuXkmZCFR19" type="topic">sublimits</rs>, provide for banning
                    heavy <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                        <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBMs</rs>
                    </gloss>, and avoid discussion of the complete elimination of <rs type="topic"
                        corresp="recr08QgEMEm1Bk04">ballistic missiles</rs> since these initial
                    reductions are our highest priority and because, for tactical reasons, we have
                    determined the complete elimination of <rs type="topic"
                        corresp="recr08QgEMEm1Bk04">ballistic missiles</rs> should more
                    appropriately be discussed in the <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N"
                        >Defense and Space</rs> forum.</p>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Issues</p>
                <p>The attached instructions are not agreed by all agencies. Two issues exist. The
                    first concerns our position that <rs type="topic" corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID"
                        >mobile</rs>
                    <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                        <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBMs</rs>
                    </gloss> should be banned for <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic"
                        >verification</rs> and stability reasons. <hi rendition="simple_italic">
                        <orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">State</orgName>
                    </hi> believes that the recent <rs type="topic" corresp="recCgPN2725pAs6HG"
                        >PEACEKEEPER</rs> decision means that our <rs type="topic"
                        corresp="recbm2CDfl6YlSCnq">modernization</rs> program and negotiating
                    position are inconsistent and that, therefore, we should alter our negotiating
                    position to permit <rs type="topic" corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID">mobile
                        missiles</rs>. <hi rendition="simple_italic">All other agencies</hi> oppose
                    changing position now. We agree.</p>
                <p>We have been stressing <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic"
                        >verification</rs> of <rs type="topic" corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID">mobile
                        missiles</rs>; the Soviets have not been prepared to discuss the subject
                    seriously. If we now accept <rs type="topic" corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID"
                        >mobile</rs> missile deployment, with no quid from the Soviets and no
                    progress on <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">verification</rs>, we
                    will lend credence to the view that the <rs type="event"
                        corresp="recrvfeHjk0YIZ1si">Administration</rs> has been wounded by <rs
                        type="event" corresp="reczBdFtXt9g39SHd">Iran</rs> and is eager for an
                    agreement to restore its prestige.</p>
                <p>As a possible compromise, <hi rendition="simple_italic">Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="recJgMRnt6OpkXR5T">Lehman</persName>
                    </hi> has suggested language authorizing detailed discussions of how mobiles
                    might be treated <hi rendition="simple_italic">if</hi> allowed. We believe that
                    sufficient flexibility now exists to do this and that we should retain the
                    existing instructions for now.</p>
                <p>The second <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss> issue is minor and involves the wording of a prohibition against
                    concealment. <gloss target="#t_CIA_1">
                        <orgName corresp="recrGZfmTCYX9A5jf">CIA</orgName>
                    </gloss> favors a ban on concealment which impedes <rs
                        corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">verification</rs>; <gloss
                        target="#t_OSD_1">
                        <orgName corresp="recoMngX7uLPacWDx">OSD</orgName>
                    </gloss> says that is too similar to <gloss target="#t_SALT_1">
                        <rs corresp="rec6OIA4luUvtBKNn" type="event">SALT</rs>
                    </gloss>
                    <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM">II</rs> and thus too
                    ambiguous. They favor a ban on <hi rendition="simple_italic">any</hi>
                    concealment of systems limited by <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss>. While the <gloss target="#t_OSD_1">
                        <orgName corresp="recoMngX7uLPacWDx">OSD</orgName>
                    </gloss> concern is real and will need to be considered when we address treaty
                    text, their formulation is excessive and would impinge on legitimate military
                    practice. Thus we favor the <gloss target="#t_CIA_1">
                        <orgName corresp="recrGZfmTCYX9A5jf">CIA</orgName>
                    </gloss> formulation.</p>
                <pb facs="0823" n="796" xml:id="pg_796"/>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendations</p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="simple_italic">OK</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="simple_italic">No</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>That existing guidance to ban <rs type="topic"
                                corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID">mobile missiles</rs> be retained.<note
                                n="11" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn11">
                                <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> initialed
                                his approval.</note>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>That guidance on concealment accept the <gloss target="#t_CIA_1">
                                <orgName corresp="recrGZfmTCYX9A5jf">CIA</orgName>
                            </gloss> formulation banning only concealment which impedes <rs
                                corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">verification</rs>.<note
                                n="12" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn12">
                                <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> initialed
                                his approval.</note>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>That you approve the proposed <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                                <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                            </gloss> negotiating instructions as modified above.<note n="13"
                                place="foot" xml:id="d181fn13">
                                <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> initialed
                                his approval.</note>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </frus:attachment>
            <frus:attachment xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
                <note>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Attachment</hi>
                </note>
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Paper Prepared in the <orgName
                            corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security Council</orgName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="14" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn14">Secret. Prepared by <persName
                            corresp="recASjYJjIDTjOXpN">Tobey</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="simple_right #right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian"
                            notAfter="1987-01-14T10:30:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1987-01-12T23:59:59-05:00">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rendition="simple_centre">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and Space</rs>
                    Instructions—Round VII</p>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
                <p>The attached instructions<note n="15" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn15">Attached but
                        not printed is a draft telegram with instructions on <rs type="event"
                            corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and Space</rs>.</note> are agreed to
                    by all agencies. They reiterate our existing <rs type="event"
                        corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and Space</rs> proposal, based on your
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recY5TBKXKBIuAnWc">Reykjavik</rs> discussions,
                    including the conditions under which we would accept a commitment through 1996
                    not to withdraw from the <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>
                    <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recKv8RyteDQ8sLn9">Treaty</rs> in
                    return for a 50% <rs type="topic" corresp="recHoFOsQcM4e5M4k">reduction in
                        strategic forces</rs> in five years, the complete elimination of all
                    offensive <rs type="topic" corresp="recr08QgEMEm1Bk04">ballistic missiles</rs>
                    by the end of 1996, and the right to deploy advanced <rs type="compound-subject"
                        corresp="recKKNyP9NHSwF6fs">strategic defenses</rs> after that time.</p>
                <p>There are no issues involved with these instructions.</p>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="simple_italic">OK</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="simple_italic">No</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>________</cell>
                        <cell>________</cell>
                        <cell>That you approve the proposed <rs type="event"
                                corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and Space</rs> negotiating
                                instructions.<note n="16" place="foot" xml:id="d181fn16">
                                <persName corresp="rech6OQ6N5EdBVhDo">Carlucci</persName> initialed
                                approval on behalf of <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq"
                                    >Reagan</persName>.</note>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </frus:attachment>
